# Expense Tracker System

## Project Overview

The Expense Tracker System is a simple web-based application developed using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It helps users manage their daily income and expenses efficiently. The application performs basic CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations and stores data using the browser's Local Storage.

---

# Objectives

* Manage daily income and expense records.
* Calculate the available balance automatically.
* View transaction history.
* Learn front-end web development concepts.
* Build a simple expense management application.

---

# Technologies Used

* HTML5
* CSS3
* JavaScript (ES6)
* Browser Local Storage

---

# Features

* User Login
* Add Income
* Add Expense
* View Transaction History
* Delete Transaction
* Automatic Balance Calculation
* Local Storage Support
* Responsive User Interface

---

# ER Diagram

```text
+---------------------------+
|           USER            |
+---------------------------+
| User_ID (Primary Key)     |
| Username                  |
| Password                  |
+---------------------------+
            |
            | Performs
            |
+---------------------------+
|       TRANSACTION         |
+---------------------------+
| Transaction_ID (PK)       |
| User_ID (FK)              |
| Title                     |
| Type                      |
| Amount                    |
| Date                      |
+---------------------------+
```

### Entity Description

| Attribute      | Description           |
| -------------- | --------------------- |
| User_ID        | Unique User ID        |
| Username       | User Login Name       |
| Password       | User Password         |
| Transaction_ID | Unique Transaction ID |
| Title          | Transaction Title     |
| Type           | Income / Expense      |
| Amount         | Transaction Amount    |
| Date           | Transaction Date      |

